# Performance

- Use React.memo for components with expensive renders - memoize when props are stable
- Use useMemo for expensive computations - cache derived values
- Use useCallback for stable function references - prevent unnecessary re-renders
- Code split large routes - use React.lazy and Suspense
- Avoid inline object/function creation in render - creates new references each render
- Use proper keys in lists - stable, unique identifiers
- Debounce/throttle user input handlers - prevent excessive API calls
- Optimize images - use appropriate formats and sizes
- Minimize bundle size - use tree shaking, remove unused code
- Profile performance with React DevTools - identify bottlenecks before optimizing
